<HEADLINE>
FT  21 JUL 94 / World News in Brief: Citroen eyes South Africa
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
French auto maker Citroen is considering building a R400m (Pounds 72m) car
assembly plant in South Africa. The company is negotiating about a site in
the former KwaNdebele homeland.
</TEXT>
<XX>
