</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Assurances Generales de France (AGF), the insurance company scheduled for
privatisation in autumn, yesterday confirmed it was considering the sale of
its 43 per cent stake in Banque Francaise du Commerce Exterieur (BFCE), the
specialist banking group.
AGF also verified that it was in talks with Credit Lyonnais, the troubled
